'''Achraf Hakimi Mouh''' ({{langx|ar|أشرف حكيمي موح}}, {{IPA|ar|ˈʔaʃraf ħaˈkiːmiː ˈmuːħ|pron}}; born 4 November 1998) is a <!-- Do not add a nationality, per consensus at Wikipedia:WikiProject Football -->professional [[Football player|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for {{French football updater|PSG}} club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]]. He is widely regarded as one of the best right-backs in the world.<ref name=":2">{{cite web |date=10 March 2023 |title=Ranked! The 10 best right-backs in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/ranked-10-best-right-backs-world-trent-alexander-arnold-liverpool-man-city-cancelo |access-date=3 June 2025 |website=FourFourTwo}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{cite web |date=11 November 2022 |title=The 25 best right backs in world football - ranked |url=https://www.90min.com/posts/the-25-best-right-backs-in-world-football-ranked |access-date=3 June 2025 |website=90min}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Charlie |date=5 May 2025 |title=The Best 15 Right-Backs in World Football Ranked (2025) |url=https://www.footballfancast.com/best-right-backs-football-players-in-the-world-ranked-2025/ |access-date=3 June 2025 |website=Football FanCast}}</ref>

At club level, Hakimi began playing for [[Real Madrid Castilla]] in 2016 and was promoted to the first team in 2017, won the Champions League and the [[Club World Cup]]. He was sent on a two-year loan deal to [[Bundesliga]] side [[Borussia Dortmund]], winning the [[DFL-Supercup]] in [[2019 DFL-Supercup|2019]]. He then signed with [[Serie A]] side [[Inter Milan]], helping the club win the [[2020–21 Serie A]] title, their first league title in 11 years. [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] then signed him in 2021 for a reported fee of €68 million.<ref name=":5">{{cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi Transfer History |url=https://www.footballtransfers.com/en/players/achraf-hakimi/transfer-history |access-date=25 April 2025 |website=Football Transfers}}</ref> With PSG, he won five [[Ligue 1]] titles and two [[Coupe de France|Coupes de France]], and was integral to the club winning their first [[UEFA Champions League]] titles back-to-back in [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|2025]] and [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|2026]], with the former being part of a [[continental treble]]. 

Hakimi was [[Cap (sport)|capped]] by Morocco at the [[Morocco national under-20 football team|under-20]] level, before making his senior international debut in 2016 aged 17. He was chosen in Morocco's squads for the [[FIFA World Cup]] twice (in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]]), the [[Africa Cup of Nations]] four times (in [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations|2019]], [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]], [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023]], and [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations|2025]]), and was one of three [[List of overage players in Olympic football|overage players]] selected for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Summer Olympics]] team. At the 2022 World Cup, he and Morocco made history as the first African nation ever to reach the World Cup semi-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/morocco-world-cup-run-best-moments-qatar/bltef577736db80b6e6|title='It's like a dream' - Morocco's 'unbelievable' World Cup run & best moments from Qatar|date=30 June 2023|website=Goal.com}}</ref>

Hakimi ranked 6th in the [[2025 Ballon d'Or|2025 Ballon d’Or]], the highest position ever achieved by a Moroccan player.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rollingout.com/2025/09/23/dembele-hakimi-ballon-dor-2025/|title=Dembélé wins Ballon d'Or 2025 as Hakimi makes history|date=23 September 2025|website=rollingout.com}}</ref> He was also named the 2025 [[African Player of the Year]], becoming the fifth Moroccan recipient of the award and the first since [[Mustapha Hadji]] in 1998.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 November 2025 |title=PSG defender Hakimi wins African Footballer of the Year |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/psg-defender-hakimi-wins-african-footballer-year-2025-11-19/ |access-date=19 November 2025 |website=Reuters}}</ref>

==Early life==
Hakimi was born on 4 November 1998, in Madrid, Spain, to Moroccan parents.<ref>{{Cite web |last=NicolasB|date=2025-09-26|title=Champions League, Luis Enrique, Ballon d'Or, family…Hakimi speaks his mind without any reservations|url=https://en.parisfans.fr/champions-league-luis-enrique-ballon-dor-familyhakimi-speaks-his-mind-without-any-reservations.html|access-date=2025-11-20|website=ParisFans|language=en-US|quote=Yes, I feel a great responsibility. I don’t know if I’m the most important Muslim or Arab figure; there’s Salah, too.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ahmad |first=Khemena |date=2022-12-10 |title=FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022: How Achraf Hakimi's patience paid off with stardom |url=https://gulfnews.com/the-kurator/life/fifa-world-cup-qatar-2022-how-achraf-hakimis-patience-paid-off-with-stardom-1.1670413264361 |access-date=2026-01-05 |website=Gulf News: Latest UAE news, Dubai news, Business, travel news, Dubai Gold rate, prayer time, cinema |language=en |quote=Thus, Hakimi possesses pure Arabic origins despite being raised in a European country.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |author=NicolasB |date=2025-09-26 |title=Champions League, Luis Enrique, Ballon d'Or, family…Hakimi speaks his mind without any reservations |url=https://en.parisfans.fr/champions-league-luis-enrique-ballon-dor-familyhakimi-speaks-his-mind-without-any-reservations.html |access-date=2025-11-20 |website=ParisFans |language=en-US |quote=Yes, I feel a great responsibility. I don’t know if I’m the most important Muslim or Arab figure; there’s Salah, too.}}</ref> His father, Mohamed, was a street vendor, and his mother, Saida, worked as a housewife.<ref>{{Cite web |first=Sara|last=Zouiten|publisher=Morocco World |title=Big World Cup Reception Awaits Achraf Hakimi in Morocco's Ksar el-Kebir |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/01/353461/big-world-cup-reception-awaits-achraf-hakimi-in-moroccos-ksar-el-kebir |access-date=2024-08-11 |website=www.moroccoworldnews.com |date=10 January 2023 |language=en}}</ref>  Hakimi grew up in [[Getafe]] belonging to the [[Community of Madrid]], where his family faced economic challenges.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cerezo |first=Hugo |date=2016-03-22 |title=Achraf Hakimi, Real Madrid's promising young starlet |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2016/03/22/56f12a86ca474179468b45d4.html |access-date=2025-05-15 |website=MARCA English |language=en}}</ref> At the age of 8, Hakimi joined Colonia Ofigevi, a local football club, where he began his football journey. His talent was quickly noticed, and in 2006, he joined [[Real Madrid Castilla|Real Madrid's youth academy]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi: The jet-heeled Morocco full-back, made in the Bundesliga |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/achraf-hakimi-10-things-borussia-dortmund-real-madrid-morocco-10940 |access-date=2025-05-15 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=The player, the man, the boy: welcome Hakimi! {{!}} Inter.it |url=https://www.inter.it/en/news/2020-09-09-achraf-hakimi-profile |access-date=2025-05-15 |website=www.inter.it |language=en}}</ref> He spent several years developing his skills in the academy, initially playing as a [[Midfielder|winger]] before transitioning to his more familiar role as a right-back. Hakimi has stated that although he was raised in Spain, he grew up in a household shaped by Arab and Muslim culture, which later influenced his decision to represent Morocco at international level.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi : An African Success Story From Continental Pride to Global Dominance – Rolling Stone Africa |url=https://rollingstoneafrica.com/cover-story/achraf-hakimi-an-african-success-story-from-continental-pride-to-global-dominance/ |access-date=2026-01-05 |language=en-US |quote=I chose a long time ago to represent Morocco because I grew up with Arab and Muslim culture at home}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco's Hakimi up against country of his birth at World Cup |url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/sports/moroccos-hakimi-up-against-country-his-birth-world-cup-2022-12-05/ |url-status= |quote=but it was not how I lived at home, which is the Arab culture, being Moroccan}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Real Madrid===
[[File:Real Madrid C.F. the Winner Of The Champions League in 2018 (1) (Achraf).jpg|thumb|Hakimi after winning the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League]] with [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]|left|152x152px]]

Hakimi made his debut for Real Madrid in the first match of the [[2016 International Champions Cup]], a 3–1 loss against [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.libertaddigital.com/deportes/futbol/2016-07-28/cuatro-canteranos-debutaron-con-el-primer-equipo-del-real-madrid-1276579343/ |title=Cuatro canteranos debutaron con el primer equipo del Real Madrid |trans-title=Four youth players debuted with Real Madrid's first team |newspaper=Libertad Digital |language=es |date=28 July 2016 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=7 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907032608/http://www.libertaddigital.com/deportes/futbol/2016-07-28/cuatro-canteranos-debutaron-con-el-primer-equipo-del-real-madrid-1276579343/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He subsequently returned to the B team, making his senior debut on 20 August 2016 by starting in a 3–2 [[Segunda División B]] home win against [[Real Sociedad B]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2016/08/3-2-espectacular-remontada-del-castilla-en-el-ultimo-minuto |title=3–2: Espectacular remontada del Castilla en el último minuto |trans-title=3–2: Spetacular last-minute comeback of Castilla |publisher=Real Madrid CF |language=es |date=20 August 2016 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=6 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906224009/http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2016/08/3-2-espectacular-remontada-del-castilla-en-el-ultimo-minuto |url-status=live}}</ref>

Hakimi scored his first senior goal on 25 September 2016, netting the equalizer in a 1–1 draw at [[CF Fuenlabrada|Fuenlabrada]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2016/09/1-1-achraf-da-un-punto-al-castilla-en-fuenlabrada- |title=1–1: Achraf da un punto al Castilla en Fuenlabrada |trans-title=1–1: Achraf gives a point to Castilla in Fuenlabrada |publisher=Real Madrid CF |language=es |date=25 September 2016 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=6 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906225329/http://www.realmadrid.com/noticias/2016/09/1-1-achraf-da-un-punto-al-castilla-en-fuenlabrada- |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 19 August 2017, Hakimi was promoted to the main squad as a backup to [[Dani Carvajal]] and [[Nacho (footballer, born 1990)|Nacho]], and was assigned the number 19 jersey.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://futbol.as.com/futbol/2017/08/19/primera/1503102548_085614.html |title=Achraf Hakimi se quedará con ficha del primer equipo blanco |trans-title=Achraf Hakimi will keep a place in Real’s first team |newspaper=[[Diario AS]] |language=es |date=19 August 2017 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=3 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903032240/https://futbol.as.com/futbol/2017/08/19/primera/1503102548_085614.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first team – and [[La Liga]] – debut on 1 October, starting in a 2–0 home win over [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/report?gameId=490643 |title=Isco double fuels Real Madrid to first home La Liga victory |website=[[ESPN FC]] |date=1 October 2017 |access-date=4 October 2017 |archive-date=4 October 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171004091802/http://www.espnfc.com/report?gameId=490643 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first La Liga goal on 9 December 2017 in a 5–0 win against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42295767 |title=Hakimi only sixth African player to score for Real Madrid |website=BBC Sport |first=Oluwashina |last=Okeleji |date=10 December 2017 |access-date=10 December 2017 |archive-date=13 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171213215115/http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42295767 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 12 May 2018, he scored his second goal against [[RC Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] in a 6–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44088523 |title=Real Madrid 6-0 Celta Vigo |website=BBC Sport |date=12 May 2018 |access-date=23 May 2021 |archive-date=23 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523180810/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44088523 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League]], he made two appearances under the age of 18 as Madrid won the title, their third consecutive and 13th overall.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0245-0e98d7318379-716954065574-1000--madrid-beat-liverpool-to-complete-hat-trick/ |title=Madrid beat Liverpool to complete hat-trick |publisher=UEFA |date=26 May 2018 |access-date=28 May 2018 |archive-date=30 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233343/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2018/matches/round=2000885/match=2021711/postmatch/report/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He thus became the first Moroccan to win the [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup/UEFA Champions League]] and the third Moroccan player to reach the final, after [[Hajry Redouane|Redouane Hajry]] and [[Mehdi Benatia]].

====Loan to Borussia Dortmund====
On 11 July 2018, Hakimi signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] on a two-year [[Loan (association football)|loan]] deal.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Borussia-Dortmund-sign-Achraf-Hakimi-on-loan |title=Borussia Dortmund sign Achraf Hakimi on loan |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-date=29 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210829124706/https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Borussia-Dortmund-sign-Achraf-Hakimi-on-loan |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/07/official-announcement-achraf |title=Official Announcement: Achraf |publisher=Real Madrid CF |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828120037/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/07/official-announcement-achraf |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 7–0 victory over [[1. FC Nürnberg]] on 27 September.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/borussia-dortmund-nuremberg-live-line-ups-stats-pulisic-reus-paco-alcacer-fantasy-512935.jsp |title=Marco Reus stars as breathtaking Borussia Dortmund put seven past Nuremberg |publisher=Bundesliga |access-date=29 September 2018 |archive-date=5 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605050033/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/borussia-dortmund-nuremberg-live-line-ups-stats-pulisic-reus-paco-alcacer-fantasy-512935.jsp |url-status=live}}</ref> He provided three assists in a single match for the first time in his career against [[Atlético Madrid]], in his first Champions League appearance for Dortmund.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2025093--b-dortmund-vs-atleti/ |title=Dortmund 4–0 Atletico |publisher=UEFA |access-date=26 October 2018 |archive-date=26 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026182923/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2019/matches/round=2000980/match=2025093/index.html?iv=true |url-status=live}}</ref> Hakimi scored a brace against [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] in the group stage of the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] on 2 October 2019, his first goals in the competition.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2027043--slavia-praha-vs-dortmund/?referrer=%2Fuefachampionsleague%2Fseason%3D2020%2Fmatches%2Fround%3D2001140%2Fmatch%3D2027043%2F |title=Visitors ease to victory in Prague |publisher=UEFA |date=2 October 2019 |access-date=31 May 2020 |archive-date=30 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210830064424/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2027043--slavia-praha-vs-dortmund/?referrer=%2Fuefachampionsleague%2Fseason%3D2020%2Fmatches%2Fround%3D2001140%2Fmatch%3D2027043%2F |url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 November 2019, Hakimi scored another brace in the second half to turn a 0–2 deficit against [[Inter Milan]] to a 3–2 win at the [[Westfalenstadion]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-inter-milan-champions-league-live-line-ups-stats-sancho-lukaku-7916 |title=Achraf Hakimi-inspired Borussia Dortmund pull off remarkable comeback to beat Inter Milan |publisher=Bundesliga |date=5 November 2019 |access-date=30 June 2020 |archive-date=31 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831023835/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-inter-milan-champions-league-live-line-ups-stats-sancho-lukaku-7916 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In February 2020, Hakimi set a Bundesliga speed record when he was clocked at 36.48&nbsp;km/h (22.67&nbsp;mph) in a match against [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]], beating the old league record which he had set against [[RB Leipzig]] three months prior at 36.2&nbsp;km/h (22.5&nbsp;mph).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.managingmadrid.com/2020/5/29/21274734/achraf-sets-bundesliga-speed-record-real-madrid-2020 |title=Achraf sets Bundesliga speed record |website=Managing Madrid |date=29 May 2020 |access-date=31 May 2020 |archive-date=28 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210828234016/https://www.managingmadrid.com/2020/5/29/21274734/achraf-sets-bundesliga-speed-record-real-madrid-2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 May, after scoring in the club's 6–1 away win over [[SC Paderborn 07|SC Paderborn]], he removed his shirt to reveal a shirt with the message "Justice for [[George Floyd]]".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52867783 |title=SC Paderborn 1–6 Borussia Dortmund |date=31 May 2020 |access-date=31 May 2020 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=31 May 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200531191613/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/52867783 |url-status=live}}</ref> His teammate, [[Jadon Sancho]], revealed a similar shirt after scoring as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/thuram-sancho-hakimi-bundesliga-protests-unrest-in-us/1d3sthm85ywp21f5j5lr73vwwg |title=Thuram, Sancho and Hakimi lead Bundesliga protests amid ongoing unrest in U.S. |website=Goal.com |date=31 May 2020 |access-date=31 May 2020 |archive-date=30 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210830035316/https://www.goal.com/en/news/thuram-sancho-hakimi-bundesliga-protests-unrest-in-us/1d3sthm85ywp21f5j5lr73vwwg |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Inter Milan===
On 2 July 2020, Hakimi signed for [[Serie A]] club Inter Milan on a five-year contract,<ref>{{cite press release|date=2 July 2020|title=Achraf Hakimi joins Inter|publisher=Inter Milan|url=https://www.inter.it/en/news/2020/07/02/hakimi-inter-official.html|access-date=2 July 2020|archive-date=18 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210618094822/https://www.inter.it/en/news/2020/07/02/hakimi-inter-official.html|url-status=live}}</ref> with a reported fee of around €40 million.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Inter complete €40m Hakimi signing as full-back leaves Real Madrid|url=https://www.goal.com/en-ie/news/real-madrid-officially-announce-transfer-of-hakimi-to-inter/1rqrdifae73s11wu9uc5f2ed0n|access-date=4 July 2020|website=Goal.com|archive-date=4 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200704195132/https://www.goal.com/en-ie/news/real-madrid-officially-announce-transfer-of-hakimi-to-inter/1rqrdifae73s11wu9uc5f2ed0n|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut on 26 September and provided an assist in a 4–3 win against [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] in the Serie A.<ref>{{Cite news|date=26 September 2020|title=Inter hit two late goals to beat Fiorentina 4-3|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-int-fio-report-idUKKBN26H0ZN|access-date=6 March 2021|archive-date=9 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210709195128/https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-int-fio-report-idUKKBN26H0ZN|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in the subsequent league game against [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]], which Inter won 5–2.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Benevento vs. Internazionale - Football Match Report - September 30, 2020 - ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=583154|access-date=6 March 2021|publisher=ESPN|archive-date=6 October 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201006170910/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=583154|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
[[File:FC Salzburg gegen Paris Saint-Germain UEFA Champions League 58.jpg|thumb|upright|Hakimi in a 2024 [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match with [[Paris Saint-Germain]]]]
Hakimi signed for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) on 6 July 2021 on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/achraf-hakimi-signs-for-paris-saint-germain-until-2026 |title=Achraf Hakimi signs for Paris Saint-Germain |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |date=6 July 2021 |access-date=6 July 2021 |archive-date=7 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210707015100/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/achraf-hakimi-signs-for-paris-saint-germain-until-2026 |url-status=live}}</ref> The transfer fee paid by PSG was reported by ''[[The Guardian]]'' to be an initial €60 million, potentially rising by €11 million in add-ons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jul/06/sergio-ramos-to-have-psg-medical-as-club-prepare-triple-signing-hakimi-donnarumma |title=PSG sign full-back Achraf Hakimi with Ramos and Donnarumma set to follow |first=Fabrizio |last=Romano |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=6 July 2021 |access-date=6 July 2021 |archive-date=23 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210823154006/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jul/06/sergio-ramos-to-have-psg-medical-as-club-prepare-triple-signing-hakimi-donnarumma |url-status=live}}</ref> Hakimi made his Ligue 1 debut on 7 August, playing the entire ninety minutes and scoring his first goal for the club against [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202122/troyes-v-paris-saint-germain?tab=commentary |title=Troyes V Paris Saint-Germain |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C. |date=7 August 2021 |access-date=7 August 2021 |archive-date=7 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210807211303/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/fixtures-and-results/202122/troyes-v-paris-saint-germain?tab=commentary |url-status=live}}</ref> He received his first red card in a 0–0 draw against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on 24 August.<ref>{{cite news |title=PSG's Hakimi receives first Ligue 1 red in Marseille draw |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/psgs-hakimi-receives-first-ligue-1-red-in-marseille-draw/zizmqw3o7aao1q3e3ha4xlp9b |access-date=26 October 2021 |website=Goal.com |archive-date=26 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026092950/https://www.goal.com/en/news/psgs-hakimi-receives-first-ligue-1-red-in-marseille-draw/zizmqw3o7aao1q3e3ha4xlp9b |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 September, Hakimi scored twice in a 2–1 victory against [[FC Metz|Metz]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Hakimi double saves PSG at Metz to stretch perfect Ligue 1 start |url=https://www.goal.com/en-cm/news/hakimi-double-saves-psg-at-metz-to-stretch-perfect-ligue-1/1nfzot46ephmg1m11qdi3upocn |access-date=7 March 2022 |website=Goal.com |archive-date=7 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220307154258/https://www.goal.com/en-cm/news/hakimi-double-saves-psg-at-metz-to-stretch-perfect-ligue-1/1nfzot46ephmg1m11qdi3upocn |url-status=live}}</ref> In his first season at PSG, he won a Ligue 1 title, his second league title in a row.<ref>{{cite news |author1=Jacob Whitehead |author2=Luke Bosher |title=PSG crowned Ligue 1 champions after draw against Lens |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4179531/2022/04/22/psg-crowned-ligue-1-champions-after-messi-secures-draw-against-lens/ |access-date=27 February 2023 |website=The Athletic |date=31 August 2022 |archive-date=27 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230227050156/https://theathletic.com/4179531/2022/04/22/psg-crowned-ligue-1-champions-after-messi-secures-draw-against-lens/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 14 February 2023, Hakimi was nominated for the 2022 [[FIFPro#FIFA FIFPRO Men's World 11|FIFA FIFPRO World 11]].<ref>{{cite web |date=14 February 2023 |title=Achraf Hakimi among best players of 2022, FIFPRO |url=https://en.hespress.com/58639-achraf-hakimi-among-best-players-of-2022-fifpro.html |access-date=14 February 2023 |website=HESPRESS |archive-date=14 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230214115354/https://en.hespress.com/58639-achraf-hakimi-among-best-players-of-2022-fifpro.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Rahhou |first=Jihane |title=Achraf Hakimi Nominated for 2022 FIFA FIFPRO World 11 |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/02/354024/achraf-hakimi-nominated-for-2022-fifa-fifpro-world-11 |access-date=14 February 2023 |website=Morocco World News |archive-date=13 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230213225732/https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/02/354024/achraf-hakimi-nominated-for-2022-fifa-fifpro-world-11 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 September 2023, Hakimi scored a goal in a 2–0 victory against his former club Dortmund in the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League]], thus earning a spot on the UEFA's Team of Week.<ref>{{cite news |title=Morocco's Achraf Hakimi in UEFA's Team of Week |url=https://www.mapnews.ma/en/actualites/sport/moroccos-achraf-hakimi-uefas-team-week |access-date=25 September 2023 |website=MapNews |date=21 September 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2023 |title=Morocco's Achraf Hakimi in UEFA's team of week |url=https://en.hespress.com/71417-moroccos-achraf-hakimi-in-uefas-team-of-week.html |access-date=25 September 2023 |website=HESPRESS}}</ref> On 1 November 2023, Hakimi was nominated for the 2023 [[African Footballer of the Year]] by [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]].<ref>{{cite news |date=11 January 2023 |title=CAF announces CAF Awards 2023 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-caf-awards-2023-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=1 November 2023 |website=CAF}}</ref> On 24 October 2024, Hakimi along with his international teammate [[Soufiane Rahimi]], were nominated for the 2024 [[African Footballer of the Year|African Footballer of the Year award]].<ref>{{cite web |last=El Masaiti |first=Amira |date=24 October 2024 |title=Moroccans Hakimi and Rahimi Nominated for CAF Player of the Year Award |url=https://en.hespress.com/94035-moroccans-hakimi-and-rahimi-nominated-for-caf-player-of-the-year-award.html |access-date=4 November 2024 |website=HESPRESS}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=CAF announces #CAFAwards24 Nominees for Men's Categories |url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-announces-cafawards24-nominees-for-men-s-categories/ |access-date=4 November 2024 |website=CAF announces #CAFAwards24 Nominees for Men’s Categories}}</ref>

On 8 February 2025, Hakimi extended his contract with Paris Saint-Germain until 2029.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/achraf-hakimi-we-have-big-things-to-achieve-together-psg-equipe-premiere-interview-2024-2025 |title=Achraf Hakimi: "We have big things to achieve together" |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |date=8 February 2025 }}</ref> On 7 May 2025, Hakimi scored PSG's second goal in a 2–1 win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League semi-final]], securing their place in the final for the second time in the competition's history.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hytner |first=David |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/may/07/hakimi-seals-paris-saint-germains-final-spot-as-bold-arsenal-fall-short |title=Hakimi seals PSG's Champions League final spot as bold Arsenal fall short |work=The Guardian |date=7 May 2025 }}</ref> On 24 May, he netted a goal in a 3–0 win over [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] in the [[2025 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cn8z037rrrlt |title=PSG 3–0 Reims |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 May 2025 }}</ref> On 31 May, he opened the scoring in the [[2025 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]], contributing to a dominant 5–0 victory over his former club Inter Milan, becoming PSG’s first Champions League final goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ogden |first=Mark |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45408435/champions-league-final-psg-inter-milan-win-first-title-record |title=Champions League final: PSG rout Inter Milan in record win for 1st title |publisher=ESPN |date=31 May 2025 }}</ref> He became the second Moroccan to play a [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup/Champions League]] final (after [[Hajry Redouane]] in [[1988 European Cup final|1988]] with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]), the first Moroccan (and seventh African) to score in a [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup/Champions League]] final,<ref>{{Cite news |title=FULL LIST: Six African players who have scored in UEFA Champions League Finals |url=https://thenationonlineng.net/full-list-six-african-players-who-have-scored-in-uefa-champions-league-finals/ |location=Lagos, Nigeria|newspaper=[[The Nation (Nigeria)|The Nation]]|date=22 January 2025 |access-date=3 August 2025}}</ref> and the second Moroccan ever (after [[Ayoub El Kaabi]] in the [[2024 UEFA Europa Conference League final|2024 Europa Conference League final]]) to score in an [[UEFA club competitions|UEFA club competition]] final.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Nine African Stars Who've Score In European Finals |url=https://www.soccerladuma.co.za/international/african-football/the-nine-african-stars-whove-score-in-european-finals-20240530 |website=Soccer Laduma |date=26 November 2024 |access-date=3 August 2025}}</ref> Hakimi's performances across the season led to him emerging as a contender for the [[2025 Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Achraf Hakimi emerges as strong Ballon d'Or contender after stellar season |url=https://en.yabiladi.com/articles/details/171502/achraf-hakimi-emerges-strong-ballon.html |website=Yabiladi |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250712145532/https://en.yabiladi.com/articles/details/171502/achraf-hakimi-emerges-strong-ballon.html |archive-date=12 July 2025 |access-date=19 July 2025 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=5 July 2025 |title=Hakimi for the Ballon d'Or? The Paris full-back's unique record 🤯 |url=https://onefootball.com/de/news/hakimi-for-the-ballon-dor-the-paris-full-backs-unique-record-41337440 |access-date=19 July 2025 |website=OneFootball}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=« Il est, pour moi, le Ballon d'Or de cette saison » : Hervé Renard donne sa préférence à Achraf Hakimi |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/-il-est-pour-moi-le-ballon-d-or-de-cette-saison-herve-renard-donne-sa-preference-a-achraf-hakimi/1578981 |access-date=19 July 2025 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref>

In the [[2025–26 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2025–26 season]], Hakimi won both the [[2025–26 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] title and the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] after a penalty shootout victory over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|final]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2026/05/311878/hakimis-psg-beat-arsenal-on-penalties-to-retain-champions-league-title/ |title=Hakimi’s PSG Beat Arsenal on Penalties to Retain Champions League Title |publisher=Morocco World News |date=30 May 2026 }}</ref> The latter marked his third Champions League title, equaling [[Samuel Eto'o]]'s record for the most titles won by an African player.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ditlhobolo |first=Austin |url=https://africanfootball.com/news/838607/Hakimi-equals-Etoo-African-UCL-Legend-Status-unlocked |title=Hakimi equals Eto'o: African UCL Legend Status unlocked! |publisher=African Football |date=31 May 2026 }}</ref> It was also the 19th major trophy of his career, surpassing the totals of both Eto'o and [[Yaya Touré]] to become the most decorated African footballer in history.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2026/05/312163/champions-league-psg-world-celebrate-hakimi-as-record-breaker/ |title=Champions League: PSG, World Celebrate Hakimi as Record Breaker |publisher=Morocco World News |date=31 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Por-Mar (3).jpg|thumb|Hakimi (right) vs Portugal's [[Bernardo Silva]] (left) at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]
After representing Morocco at [[Morocco national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Morocco national under-20 football team|under-20]] levels,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sport.le360.ma/maroc/videos-portrait-achraf-hakimi-une-premiere-en-grandes-pompes-40998 |title=Achraf Hakimi, une première en grandes pompes |trans-title=Achraf Hakimi, a first-teamer with great future |website=Le360 Sport |language=fr |date=2 September 2017 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=12 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140608/http://sport.le360.ma/maroc/videos-portrait-achraf-hakimi-une-premiere-en-grandes-pompes-40998 |url-status=live}}</ref> Hakimi made his debut for [[Morocco national under-23 football team|the under-23s]] on 5 June 2016, in a 1–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] win over [[Cameroon national under-23 football team|Cameroon U23s]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mountakhab.net/www/modules/fiches_joueurs/feuille_match.php?id=1229622 |title=Rapport de match: Maroc Olympique 1–0 Cameroun Olympique |trans-title=Match report: Morocco Olympic 1–0 Cameroon Olympic |website=Mountakhab.net |language=fr |date=5 June 2017 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906224616/http://mountakhab.net/www/modules/fiches_joueurs/feuille_match.php?id=1229622 |archive-date=6 September 2017}}</ref> He made his full international debut on 11 October 2016, coming on as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Fouad Chafik]] in a 4–0 win against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2016/10/12/57fe0b3aca474109758b4640.html |title=Achraf Hakimi becomes Real Madrid's first Moroccan international |newspaper=Marca |location=Spain |date=12 October 2016 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=28 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828103117/http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2016/10/12/57fe0b3aca474109758b4640.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first international goal on 1 September 2017, netting the fourth in a 6–0 home routing of [[Mali national football team|Mali]].<ref name="firstintlgoal">{{cite news |url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2017/09/02/59aa6e6122601dbd438b4573.html |title=Real Madrid's Achraf scores on his competitive Morocco debut |newspaper=Marca |location=Spain |date=2 September 2017 |access-date=6 September 2017 |archive-date=6 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906100840/http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2017/09/02/59aa6e6122601dbd438b4573.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

In May 2018, he was named in [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]]'s preliminary [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] and on 4 June he was named in the final 23-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://talksport.com/football/world-cup-2018-morocco-announce-preliminary-26-man-squad-180518283174 |title=World Cup 2018: Morocco announce preliminary 26-man squad |publisher=Talksport |date=18 May 2018 |access-date=10 June 2018 |archive-date=13 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713055536/https://talksport.com/football/376391/world-cup-2018-morocco-announce-preliminary-26-man-squad-180518283174/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.frmf.ma/fr/article/coupe-du-monde-2018-liste-finale-des-vingt-trois-lions-de-latlas |title=Coupe du monde 2018: liste finale des vingt trois Lions de l'Atlas |trans-title=2018 World Cup: final list of twenty-three Atlas Lions |publisher=[[Royal Moroccan Football Federation]] |date=4 June 2018 |access-date=4 June 2018 |language=fr |archive-date=12 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140217/http://www.frmf.ma/fr/article/coupe-du-monde-2018-liste-finale-des-vingt-trois-lions-de-latlas}}</ref>

Hakimi was also called up for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] in Cameroon.<ref>{{cite news |date=23 December 2021 |title=Afcon 2021: Hakim Ziyech not recalled to Morocco squad for tournament in Cameroon |publisher=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/africa/59769523 |access-date=24 December 2021 |archive-date=23 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211223204608/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/africa/59769523 |url-status=live}}</ref> He started all of his matches in the group stages.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Africa Cup of Nations |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/morocco-vs-ghana/teams/457198 |access-date=28 January 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=28 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128124712/https://www.skysports.com/football/morocco-vs-ghana/teams/457198 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Africa Cup of Nations |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/morocco-vs-comoros/teams/457210 |access-date=28 January 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=28 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128124709/https://www.skysports.com/football/morocco-vs-comoros/teams/457210 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored from a free kick in a 2–2 draw against [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gabon v Morocco Match Report, 18/01/2022, Africa Cup of Nations |url=https://www.goal.com/en/match/gabon-v-morocco/7o6548ig1nn0zm2jg1tsh7504 |access-date=28 January 2022 |website=www.goal.com |archive-date=28 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128124705/https://www.goal.com/en/match/gabon-v-morocco/7o6548ig1nn0zm2jg1tsh7504 |url-status=live}}</ref> He started in the round of 16 against [[Malawi national football team|Malawi]], scoring a free kick in the 70th minute to earn his team a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco 2–1 Malawi: Achraf Hakimi free-kick completes Morocco comeback to reach AFCON quarter-finals |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/morocco-vs-malawi/report/457235 |access-date=28 January 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=27 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220127100830/https://www.skysports.com/football/morocco-vs-malawi/report/457235 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 10 November 2022, Hakimi was named in Morocco's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web |title=Morocco World Cup 2022 squad: Who's in and who's out |url=https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=Goal.com |archive-date=10 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221110144143/https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=10 November 2022 |title=Moroccan coach unveils list of 26 Atlas Lions in 2022 World Cup |url=https://en.hespress.com/52697-moroccan-coach-unveils-list-of-26-atlas-lions-in-2022-world-cup.html |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=hespress.com |archive-date=10 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221110144117/https://en.hespress.com/52697-moroccan-coach-unveils-list-of-26-atlas-lions-in-2022-world-cup.html |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored the winning penalty with a [[Panenka (penalty kick)|panenka]] style shot in a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] (his birth country) in the round of 16, securing a place for his country in the quarter-finals and ultimately paving the way for his team to reach the semi-finals of the competition as the first African nation to do so in history.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi converts a penalty kick to send Morocco to the quarterfinals {{!}} 2022 FIFA World Cup |url=https://www.foxsports.com/watch/play-6129adcad00004b |access-date=2022-12-06 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US |archive-date=6 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221206193945/https://www.foxsports.com/watch/play-6129adcad00004b |url-status=live }}</ref> Morocco was also the first Arab country to reach the semi-finals, and the second Muslim one after [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in [[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]].

On 28 December 2023, Hakimi was amongst the 27 players selected by coach [[Walid Regragui]] to represent Morocco in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] in Ivory Coast.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-28 |title=Regragui unveils 27 player list for Morocco's participation in CAN 2023 |url=https://en.hespress.com/77181-regragui-unveils-27-player-list-for-moroccos-participation-in-can-2023.html |access-date=2023-12-29 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-28 |title=Regragui names 27 provisional players for AFCON |url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-africa-cup-of-nations/news/regragui-names-27-provisional-players-for-afcon/ |access-date=2023-12-29 |website=CAF |language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored a goal in a 1–1 group stage draw against [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-01-21 |title=Morocco vs DR Congo 1:1 – AFCON 2023, as it happened |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/liveblog/2024/1/21/morocco-vs-dr-congo-afcon-2023-favourites-live-updates-commentary-coverage-goals |access-date=2024-02-11 |website=Al Jazeera |language=en-GB}}</ref> In the round of 16, he missed a penalty in a 2–0 loss to [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-01-30 |title=Afcon: Hakimi misses penalty and Amrabat sent off as South Africa stun Morocco |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/jan/30/mali-burkina-faso-afcon-ivory-coast-morocco-south-africa |access-date=2025-04-25 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

On 4 July 2024, Hakimi was included in the [[Morocco national under-23 football team|Moroccan Olympic football team]] for the [[2024 Olympics]] in France as one of their three [[List of overage players in Olympic football|overage players]] and was selected as captain for the team.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://frmf.ma/%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b3%d9%8a%d8%af-%d8%b7%d8%a7%d8%b1%d9%82-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b3%d9%83%d8%aa%d9%8a%d9%88%d9%8a-%d9%8a%d9%83%d8%b4%d9%81-%d8%b9%d9%86-%d9%82%d8%a7%d8%a6%d9%85%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d9%84%d8%a7/ |title=السيد طارق السكتيوي يكشف عن قائمة اللاعبين المتوجه إلى باريس |trans-title=Mr. Tariq Al-Saktiwi reveals the list of players heading to Paris |language=ar |publisher=Royal Moroccan Football Federation |date=4 July 2024}}</ref> He recorded an assist and a goal in victories against [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq]] and the [[United States men's national under-23 soccer team|United States]] respectively.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/olympics/live/c9782p2d59qt |title=Morocco U23 vs Iraq U23: Olympics |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/olympics/live/clwyew1rp72t |title=Morocco U23 vs United States U23: Olympics |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2 August 2024}}</ref> He scored again in Morocco's 6–0 win over [[Egypt national under-23 football team|Egypt]] in the bronze medal match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/olympics/live/c3w66nwv2l6t |title=Egypt U23 vs Morocco U23: Olympics |publisher=BBC Sport |date=8 August 2024}}</ref>

In May 2025, Achraf Hakimi was the favorite for the RFI "Marc-Vivien Foé" prize, which he ended up winning.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique-foot/20250512-prix-marc-vivien-fo%C3%A9-2025-le-sacre-du-marocain-achraf-hakimi |title=Prix Marc-Vivien Foé 2025: le sacre du Marocain Achraf Hakimi |publisher=Radio France International |date=12 May 2025}}</ref>

[[File:Achraf Hakimi vs Niger (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.80|right|Hakimi with [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in 2025]]
In October 2025, Hakimi's Morocco broke the [[List of world association football records|world record for the longest winning streak in international football]], surpassing [[Spain national football team|Spain]]'s previous mark of 15 consecutive victories. With a 1–0 win over [[Congo national football team|Congo]] in [[Rabat]], they extended their unbeaten run to 16 in all competitions, including World Cup qualifiers and friendlies.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gleeson |first=Mark |date=14 October 2025 |title=Morocco beat Congo to surpass Spain's wins record |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/morocco-beat-congo-surpass-spains-wins-record-2025-10-14/ |access-date=15 October 2025 |website=Reuters}}</ref> Despite carrying an injury, he was named in Morocco's squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]], which was hosted on home soil.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/2625906/sport |title=Morocco include injured captain Hakimi in AFCON squad |publisher=The Arab News |date=11 December 2025 }}</ref> On 4 January 2026, he provided the assist for the only goal in a 1–0 victory over [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web |last=Miller |first=Ben |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6w2767d46t |title=Morocco 1–0 Tanzania |publisher=BBC Sport |date=4 January 2026 }}</ref> Morocco went on to lose to Senegal in the final, with the title being awarded to Morocco two months after the final whistle.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/news/caf-appeal-board-media-statement/|title=CAF Appeal Board Media Statement|website=CAF Appeal Board Media Statement}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite news |last=Aarons |first=Ed |date=2026-03-17 |title=Senegal stripped of Africa Cup of Nations title over walkout protest in final |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2026/mar/17/senegal-stripped-of-africa-cup-of-nations-title-over-protest-in-chaotic-final |access-date=2026-03-18 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

==Player profile==
Upon signing for Borussia Dortmund, Hakimi was described as a right-sided attacking [[Full-back (association football)|full-back]] or wing-back who had previously trained as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] and could also play as a defender. His playing style included speed, physical strength, tactical awareness, technical ability, and the capacity to play long passes from defense.<ref>{{cite web |title=Achraf |work=Real Madrid C.F. - Web Oficial |url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/football/squad/achraf-hakimi |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170905181450/http://www.realmadrid.com/en/football/squad/achraf-hakimi |archive-date=5 September 2017 |access-date=6 September 2017 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/2666543/2021/06/22/how-achraf-hakimi-could-be-potent-source-goals-creativity-for-chelsea/ |title=How Achraf Hakimi could be a potent source of goals and creativity for Chelsea |work=The Athletic |last1=Twomey |first1=Liam |last2=Carey |first2=Mark |date=22 June 2021 |access-date=2 November 2021 |archive-date=2 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211102015534/https://theathletic.com/2666543/2021/06/22/how-achraf-hakimi-could-be-potent-source-goals-creativity-for-chelsea/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Some sources have referred to him as one of the best right-backs in the world.<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":4" />

==Personal life==
Hakimi is a [[Muslim]] who has performed the [[Umrah]] to [[Mecca]] multiple times. He speaks Spanish, Moroccan Arabic, French, and English.

Hakimi was married to Spanish actress of Tunisian descent [[Hiba Abouk]] from 2020 until 2023. The couple have two sons, born in 2020 and 2022.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi: 10 things on Borussia Dortmund's high-flying Real Madrid loanee |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/achraf-hakimi-10-things-borussia-dortmund-real-madrid-morocco-10940 |access-date=3 July 2020 |website=bundesliga.com |archive-date=31 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831034639/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/achraf-hakimi-10-things-borussia-dortmund-real-madrid-morocco-10940 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Borussia Dortmund's Hakimi returns to Madrid for birth of first child |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gh/news/borussia-dortmunds-hakimi-returns-to-madrid-for-birth-of/1d73w4ljv7fhe1lxcuai4fy3a9 |access-date=3 July 2020 |website=Goal.com |archive-date=31 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831023836/https://www.goal.com/en-gh/news/borussia-dortmunds-hakimi-returns-to-madrid-for-birth-of/1d73w4ljv7fhe1lxcuai4fy3a9 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 March 2023, Abouk released a statement on her [[Instagram]] account confirming that the couple had previously separated, and that they were awaiting divorce proceedings.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://english.elpais.com/spain/2023-03-28/hiba-abouk-breaks-silence-after-achraf-hakimi-accused-of-rape-i-will-always-be-on-the-side-of-the-victims.html |title=Hiba Abouk breaks silence after Achraf Hakimi accused of rape: 'I will always be on the side of the victims' |work=El País |last=Porcel |first=María |date=28 March 2023 |access-date=14 April 2023 |archive-date=30 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230330023802/https://english.elpais.com/spain/2023-03-28/hiba-abouk-breaks-silence-after-achraf-hakimi-accused-of-rape-i-will-always-be-on-the-side-of-the-victims.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Ahmad |first=Fauzan |date=2023-04-17 |title=This Is How Hakimi Outsmarted His Ex-Wife Hiza Abouk - Fifa world cup katar |url=https://fifaworldcupkatar.com/this-is-how-hakimi-outsmarted-his-ex-wife-hiza-abouk/ |access-date=2023-04-24 |language=en-US |archive-date=24 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230424052944/https://fifaworldcupkatar.com/this-is-how-hakimi-outsmarted-his-ex-wife-hiza-abouk/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> It was reported that Abouk requested more than half of Hakimi's assets and fortune, although the assets are allegedly held in his mother's name.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-04-14 |title=Achraf Hakimi ex-wife tries to claim half his fortune, discovers nothing in his name |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/sports/2023/04/14/Achraf-Hakimi-ex-wife-tries-to-claim-half-his-fortune-discovers-nothing-in-his-name |access-date=2023-04-14 |website=Al Arabiya English |language=en |archive-date=14 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230414170844/https://english.alarabiya.net/sports/2023/04/14/Achraf-Hakimi-ex-wife-tries-to-claim-half-his-fortune-discovers-nothing-in-his-name |url-status=live}}</ref> The claim was later disproven as [[fake news]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi's divorce tactics to keep fortune form ex-wife labelled 'fake news' |url=https://www.ibtimes.co.uk/achraf-hakimis-divorce-tactics-keep-fortune-form-ex-wife-labelled-fake-news-1715276 |date=20 April 2023 |website=International Business Times UK |author=Christine Caparras |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi's Ex-Wife Demanding Half of His Property Was Fake News: Report |url=https://www.news18.com/football/achraf-hakimis-ex-wife-demanding-half-of-his-property-was-fake-news-report-7668715.html|date=29 April 2023 |website=CNN-News18 |author=Ritayan Basu |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Achraf Hakimi's divorce: The swift (misogynist) journey of fake news |url=https://www.theafricareport.com/301896/ashraf-hakimis-divorce-the-swift-misogynist-journey-of-fake-news/ |date=20 April 2023 |website=The Africa Report |language=en}}</ref>

Following Hakimi's performances at the 2022 FIFA World Cup in Qatar, a football stadium in Ksar el-Kebir was named after him.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-12 |title=Morocco renames stadium after Achref Hakimi |url=https://www.africanews.com/2023/01/11/morocco-renames-stadium-after-achref-hakimi/ |access-date=2024-08-11 |website=Africanews |language=en}}</ref> He was named Arab Sportsman of the Year for 2022 at the Joy Awards in [[Riyadh]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-01-23 |title=Morocco and PSG defender Achraf Hakimi named Arab Sportsman of the Year |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/64375957 |access-date=2025-04-24 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 3 March 2023, Hakimi was indicted by an investigating judge in Paris over an allegation of rape of a 24-year-old woman, and placed under [[judicial supervision (France)|judicial supervision]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/3/3/morocco-and-psg-defender-hakimi-charged-with-rape |title=PSG's Achraf Hakimi under investigation after rape allegation |work=Al Jazeera |date=3 March 2023 |access-date=9 March 2023 |archive-date=8 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230308092723/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/3/3/morocco-and-psg-defender-hakimi-charged-with-rape |url-status=live}}</ref> He was banned from contacting his alleged victim but allowed to leave French territory.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/03/03/achraf-hakimi-france-rape/ |title=Top Moroccan soccer player charged with rape in France |newspaper=The Washington Post |first=Rick |last=Noack |date=3 March 2023 |access-date=9 March 2023 |archive-date=7 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230307020130/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/03/03/achraf-hakimi-france-rape/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Hakimi's lawyer, Fanny Colin, has stated that his client strongly denies these allegations.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-04-19 |title=Achraf Hakimi's mother, his fortune and Hiba Abouk: If he doesn't do it, he won't get rid of that woman |url=https://www.marca.com/en/lifestyle/celebrities/2023/04/19/644008edca47416b6a8b4640.html |access-date=2023-08-10 |website=MARCA |language=en}}</ref>

In October 2023, together with PSG players [[Randal Kolo Muani]], [[Ousmane Dembélé]] and [[Layvin Kurzawa]], Hakimi was handed a one-match suspension for participating in offensive chants following a victory against rivals Marseille.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-05 |title=Four PSG players suspended after offensive chants |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/38577837/four-psg-players-suspended-offensive-chants |website=ESPN |access-date=2023-10-21 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |author=<!--staff writer--> |date=2023-09-25 |title=PSG – OM. Hakimi, Dembélé et Kolo Muani risquent une suspension après des chants anti-OM |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/paris-sg/psg-om-hakimi-dembele-et-kolo-muani-risquent-une-suspension-apres-des-chants-anti-om-a8a1f318-5bbd-11ee-aaf2-4f45a6c10f18 |access-date=2024-06-14 |website=Ouest-France.fr |language=fr}}</ref>

On 12 October 2023, Hakimi, [[Didier Drogba]], [[Mikel John Obi]] and [[Sadio Mané]] were selected as Draw Assistants for the Final Draw of the TotalEnergies [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|Africa Cup of Nations Cote d'Ivoire 2023]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-12-10 |title=Drogba, Mikel, Mane and Hakimi named as star-studded Draw Assistants for the TotalEnergies CAF Africa Cup of Nations Cote d'Ivoire 2023 Final Draw |url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-africa-cup-of-nations/news/drogba-mikel-mane-and-hakimi-named-as-star-studded-draw-assistants-for-the-totalenergies-caf-africa-cup-of-nations-cote-d-ivoire-2023-final-draw/ |access-date=2023-10-12 |website=CAF |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-12 |title=Mikel, Drogba, Mane, Hakimi Named AFCON Draw Ambassadors - Naija Times |url=https://ntm.ng/2023/10/12/mikel-drogba-mane-hakimi-named-afcon-draw-ambassadors/ |access-date=2023-10-12 |language=en-US}}</ref>

